  "text": "Finally, tick-transmitted diseases are among the most frequent wildlife-related zoonoses in the northern hemisphere. The agents are varied and include tick-borne encephalitis virus, Anaplasma phagocitophylum (the causative agent of human granulocytic ehrlichiosis), Lyme disease and several others. In most of these, wildlife hosts play a role either as disease reservoirs or by increasing the tick numbers [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] .",
